post_text:
P-EBT Social Media Post
Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.
P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit http://hhs.texas.gov/pebt or call 833-613-6220.

post_text:
Governor Abbott issued an executive order closing all schools for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year. Richards ISD will continue to provide educational services, daily support, and resources for students during this time. RISD will continue to work with the commissioner of education and TEA on moving forward. We are working diligently on plans for graduation and hope to have something finalized in the upcoming weeks.

We are all very sad that we will not see your child’s smiling face each and every day. Please know that we are still committed, willing and ready to serve you and your child no matter what challenges we face. Thank you for your support and cooperation as we ensure that all members of the community in Richards ISD stay safe and healthy.

post_text:
In order to slow the spread of the coronavirus and safeguard the well-being of our students and staff, Richards ISD will remain closed through April 10th, 2020, with a plan to reevaluate on April 6th, 2020. Richards ISD is working on a plan for continuing educational services for students during this time and will share information with parents regarding this plan when it is complete.

Moving forward we will need to gather information on the best way to deliver instruction. Expect a phone call in the next few days from your child’s teacher. This is an unprecedented time for all of us.

We miss your children each and every day please know that we are still committed, willing and ready to serve you and your children no matter what challenges we face. Thank you for your support and cooperation as we ensure that all members of the community in Richards ISD stay safe and healthy.

post_text: RISD is pleased to announce the TRE-tax ratification election in support of our school passed. Thanks to all those who voted. RISD is dedicated to quality education and fiscal responsibility. This increase in tax revenue allows us to invest in retainment of quality teachers and provide a better education environment for our students. We are excited to have the support of our community as we strive for excellence in education and still maintain one of the lowest tax rates in Texas. Thank you!

post_text:
Today, school staff and officials received information regarding a threat made on a social media platform against Richards ISD. This threat was from a student attending Richards ISD. The student was removed from campus. The information was immediately reported to the proper authorities. School officials immediately alerted the Board of Trustees and are working with local law enforcement to provide for the safety and security of our students and staff. Tomorrow, students should report to class on their normal schedule.
The district will send updates if additional information becomes available.
Please feel free to contact me if you have any additional questions or concerns.

William Boyce
Superintendent
Richards ISD

Today, Sheriff Don Sowell and District Attorney Investigator John Wren joined us today to read to Pre-K through 1st grade classes. The presentations taught students about what police officers do to serve the community and help victims of crime.

Each participating student was pinned with a junior Deputy badge and given a magnet with local law enforcement contact information to take home.

Thank you!!!

Our hearts go out to everyone affected by the devastation that has been caused by Hurricane Harvey.

Due to extenuating travel conditions, Richards ISD has decided to cancel school for Thursday and Friday.

School will start on Tuesday, September 5, 2017. RISD feels this decision is in the best interest and safety for all students, parents and faculty.

Please have a safe Labor Day weekend and we look forward to seeing everyone Tuesday morning.

Update :

Richards ISD has cancelled school for Tuesday and Wednesday, August 29 & 30, 2017 due to weather conditions.

Please be cautious of flooded roads and do not attempt to cross flowing water. If you or a family member are in need of a shelter during this storm, shelters will be available at Plantersville, the Navasota Center, and the Navasota VFW. If you have any questions about shelters please contact the Grimes County Sheriff’s Office at 936-873-2151.

Hurricane Harvey Update

District administration is actively monitoring the approaching storm and has met with local law enforcement and emergency management. We will notify you via E-Notes, school website, Facebook and local news media by Sunday evening if a decision is made to adjust the start of school on Monday morning. Please be cautious of flooded roads and do not attempt to cross flowing water. If you or a family member are in need of a shelter during this storm, shelters will be available at Plantersville, the Navasota Center, and the Navasota VFW. If you have any questions about shelters please contact the Grimes County Sheriff’s Office at 936-873-2151.

post_text:
TO ALL PARENTS/GUARDIANS OF RICHARDS ISD STUDENTS:

In an effort to process absence notes more efficiently you will now send absences notes in one of the following ways:

Written note – Written notes from parents or doctor notes should be delivered to Mr. Boyce or Ms. Chance’s office. Teachers will not be responsible for collecting absence notes. Be sure your student understands this new procedure.
Email – You may find it more convenient to send an absence note via email. If you are able you can also scan doctor notes into an email and send to the school. The email address for sending an absence note is attendance@richardsisd.net

Absence notes should include the students name and the date/s of the absence.

As a reminder please get absence notes turned in as quickly as possible. A student’s absence is considered unexcused until an absence note is received. To prevent your student from having unexcused absences be sure to send a note every time they miss school (partial days included).

post_text:
E-Notes Sign Up!

New for the 2015-16 school year are District E-Notes. You can sign up for district, campus and even teacher alerts to come right to your e-mail or as a text message to your phone. You can sign up right here http://www.richardsisd.net

Many of our teachers will have e-notes for their classrooms, and coaches of sports teams may have alerts set as well. Locate your child's teacher's page, when they are up and running, to see if that teacher has E-Notes set up for their classroom or activity. And even if they don't, check back often.
